  "text": "Excuse me ma'am. Ma'am, question for you. How old were you when you became a millionaire? I'm not a millionaire. No? No, I'm a billionaire. You're a billionaire? Are you actually? How did you become a billionaire? Shaping eyebrows. I own a company called Anastasia Beverly Hills. Are you self-made? Yes, totally. So you don't come from a lot of money? No, I came here from a communist regime from Romania. I go all over the world interviewing billionaires to help the younger generation. Can I get a minute with you for the channel real quick? Absolutely. As a billionaire, what's the best financial that she would give to the younger generation? If you want to start your own business, watch the cash flow. EBITDA is everything. It's all about the profit. It's all about the profit. Don't start spending money left and right. When I started, I was driving a beat-up car that I spent $200. It didn't matter if my daughter thought that I couldn't drive her to school because the kids would make fun of her. I didn't care. I had bigger goals. The beauty industry is competitive. How did you stand out from the competition? The marketing people. Social media right now. You know, we were the first one, and this is how we scale. My daughter that worked with me in 2012, she came to me and said, Mom, maybe we'll get into this app called Instagram. And I said, okay, let's try. Let's see. So we start posting pictures of our products. It's exploded the company. So social media changed the game for you? Changed completely the game. We were the first beauty brand having a presence on Instagram. I love that. So you always have to be alert. Business changes every day. You have to adapt. You have to pay. Now, you've already built a billion-dollar company. You've became a billionaire. Are you still motivated to keep on going? Oh, I work like I can pay my rent next month. So you're working like the rents do? Oh, yes, yes. I love it. I love what I do. I don't even feel like I work. And that's the key. You have amazing advice. Thank you so much for your time. Thank you so much. I appreciate you and wish you good luck. And everybody else that is watching, believe in yourself, because you could do whatever you want. Now, I have to ask you, I connect with all the billionaires I interview. Can I get your contact? Sure.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 4.5,
      "text": "Excuse me ma'am. Ma'am, question for you. How old were you when you became a millionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 4.9,
      "end": 7.2,
      "text": "I'm not a millionaire. No? No, I'm a billionaire."
    },
    {
      "start": 7.9,
      "end": 10.8,
      "text": "You're a billionaire? Are you actually? How did you become a billionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.2,
      "end": 14.5,
      "text": "Shaping eyebrows. I own a company called Anastasia Beverly Hills."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.6,
      "end": 17.3,
      "text": "Are you self-made? Yes, totally. So you don't come from a lot of money?"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.4,
      "end": 20.2,
      "text": "No, I came here from a communist regime from Romania."
    },
    {
      "start": 20.6,
      "end": 23.0,
      "text": "I go all over the world interviewing billionaires to help the younger generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.2,
      "end": 24.6,
      "text": "Can I get a minute with you for the channel real quick?"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.8,
      "end": 28.8,
      "text": "Absolutely. As a billionaire, what's the best financial that she would give to the younger generation?"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.8,
      "end": 33.5,
      "text": "If you want to start your own business, watch the cash flow. EBITDA is everything."
    },
    {
      "start": 33.9,
      "end": 36.1,
      "text": "It's all about the profit. It's all about the profit."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.3,
      "end": 38.7,
      "text": "Don't start spending money left and right."
    },
    {
      "start": 38.9,
      "end": 42.3,
      "text": "When I started, I was driving a beat-up car that I spent $200."
    },
    {
      "start": 42.8,
      "end": 46.6,
      "text": "It didn't matter if my daughter thought that I couldn't drive her to school"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.6,
      "end": 50.4,
      "text": "because the kids would make fun of her. I didn't care. I had bigger goals."
    },
    {
      "start": 50.6,
      "end": 53.1,
      "text": "The beauty industry is competitive. How did you stand out from the competition?"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.3,
      "end": 55.7,
      "text": "The marketing people. Social media right now."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.7,
      "end": 58.1,
      "text": "You know, we were the first one, and this is how we scale."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.4,
      "end": 62.3,
      "text": "My daughter that worked with me in 2012, she came to me and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.4,
      "end": 65.7,
      "text": "Mom, maybe we'll get into this app called Instagram."
    },
    {
      "start": 66.1,
      "end": 68.3,
      "text": "And I said, okay, let's try. Let's see."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.5,
      "end": 73.3,
      "text": "So we start posting pictures of our products. It's exploded the company."
    },
    {
      "start": 73.4,
      "end": 74.9,
      "text": "So social media changed the game for you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.0,
      "end": 76.2,
      "text": "Changed completely the game."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.3,
      "end": 79.5,
      "text": "We were the first beauty brand having a presence on Instagram."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.7,
      "end": 80.1,
      "text": "I love that."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.2,
      "end": 83.4,
      "text": "So you always have to be alert. Business changes every day."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.6,
      "end": 85.7,
      "text": "You have to adapt. You have to pay."
    },
    {
      "start": 85.7,
      "end": 87.5,
      "text": "Now, you've already built a billion-dollar company."
    },
    {
      "start": 87.6,
      "end": 89.9,
      "text": "You've became a billionaire. Are you still motivated to keep on going?"
    },
    {
      "start": 90.1,
      "end": 92.5,
      "text": "Oh, I work like I can pay my rent next month."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.8,
      "end": 93.8,
      "text": "So you're working like the rents do?"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.9,
      "end": 96.5,
      "text": "Oh, yes, yes. I love it. I love what I do."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.7,
      "end": 99.1,
      "text": "I don't even feel like I work. And that's the key."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.2,
      "end": 99.9,
      "text": "You have amazing advice."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.2,
      "end": 101.0,
      "text": "Thank you so much for your time."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.0,
      "end": 103.2,
      "text": "Thank you so much. I appreciate you and wish you good luck."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.2,
      "end": 106.3,
      "text": "And everybody else that is watching, believe in yourself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 106.6,
      "end": 108.2,
      "text": "because you could do whatever you want."
    },
    {
      "start": 108.3,
      "end": 110.5,
      "text": "Now, I have to ask you, I connect with all the billionaires I interview."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.6,
      "end": 111.3,
      "text": "Can I get your contact?"
    },
    {
      "start": 111.6,
      "end": 111.9,
      "text": "Sure."
    }
  ],
